column5: Anyone been out on lake muskoka ice fishing yet? Just wondering how thick the ice is
I live in gravenhurst and gull lake is not even frozen there is ice around the edges but it's going to be two weeks of cold temps before I would even dare go out there.
No ice yet on the big lakes up here.  Going to be a while untill we have good ice on the big lakes.  Big fisher it says your from bracebridge, do you not drive around and look at the lakes yourself?
sorry my bad havent used this account for a long time  ment to change the location i moved to tronto and thanks for the update and coreyhkh whats in gull lake have never fished that lake
Panfish bass mostly it's also stocked with rainbow.
I was in the area over the weekend....going to be a while... Id assume mid-late january
ok thanks guys keep me posted.
Was out in a boat today on lake muskoka.  Lake is starting to freeze up around the muskoka river up to indian head marina, going to be awhile if we get the snow they are calling for.
hey guys just seeing if there is any ice yet.
i was thing down by the fire collage might be thick enought to fish but with thes warm temps who knows.
